indepdendent too).\n\nthe second one is that you seem to be suggesting that people *prefer* not having the features of traditional forums, because they're on platforms that don't have those features. this just seems incorrect? people were on forums because that's where people were, too, so i can't conclusively say that people *preferred* those, but that's really the thing here: people tend to use the things that they're familiar with, that exist, and that all the people are on. i think you really underestimate force of habit and network effects here, as well as the fact that 20-year-olds today might not ever have seen a phpbb forum and thus would not be familiar with the uses thereof.","children":[{"comment":{"commentId":"16bc82e9-a368-469f-a795-1dd66a2fad02","postedAtISO":"2023-01-13T02:07:35.860Z","deleted":false,"body":"that said i am now reminded of that thing about how twitter was losing its \"heavy tweeters\" in which a \"heavy tweeter\" was someone who looked at twitter almost every day and tweeted four times a week, and how these people only make up less than 10% of twitter's monthly users.\n\nbasically: more than 90% of people on twitter actually just use twitter as some sort of conksuck feed reader, i guess? with that context i'm not even sure how meaningful it is to talk about what features people want from social media if 90% of \"active\" users don't use even the core features","children":[],"postId":833874,"inReplyTo":"9b825625-9fc5-4ae0-88a6-a796b95b1409","hasCohostPlus":false,"hidden":false},"canInteract":"allowed","canEdit":"not-allowed","canHide":"not-allowed","poster":{"projectId":20068,"handle":"softfennec","displayName":"authentic soft fennec friend brand fennecs","dek":"just, like, a creature","description":"im fluffy","avatarURL":"https:\u002F\u002Fstaging.cohostcdn.org\u002Favatar\u002F20068-322af090-8746-4c57-b58e-7ee048457515-profile.png","avatarPreviewURL":"https:\u002F\u002Fstaging.cohostcdn.org\u002Favatar\u002F20068-322af090-8746-4c57-b